 In order to allow a broad spectrum of different positions to be heard, Klaus Benesch takes a look at the topic not only from the perspective of reading research and literary studies. Asking questions about the changing role of reading and the humanities in the information age also calls for broadening the perspective into the realm of social and science policy. New self-images of the humanities are needed that open up the cultural technique of reading in a new, contemporary and sustainable way in the age of digitalisation.  afunded by Hauslage-Stiftung  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aDigital Humanities. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aGeisteswissenschaft. 4aKultur. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aLeseforschung. 4aLesen. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturtheorie. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aUniversität. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftspolitik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Theory.  aCulture.  aDigital Humanities.  aDigital Media.  aHumanities.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aReading Research.  aReading.  aScience Policy.  aScience.  aTheory of Literature.  aUniversity.2 aHauslage-Stiftungefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978383945655240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839456552423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839456552/original  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  a